    <section style="margin-bottom:2rem">
      <h2>The Verdict: Right Tool for the Right Job</h2>
      <p>If you are an individual developer at a large company focused purely on writing code: Copilot or Cursor is your best option. They are optimized for that exact use case.</p>
      <p>If you are a founder or operator running a business — responsible for sales, product, engineering, and strategy simultaneously — Mekong CLI is the only tool built for your actual job description.</p>
      <p>Many founders use both: Mekong for business automation across all layers, and Copilot/Cursor for in-editor code completion when deep in engineering mode. They serve different moments in the workflow.</p>
      <p>Read the <a href="/docs/guides/quickstart">quickstart guide</a> to get Mekong running in 10 minutes, or see the <a href="/docs/pricing">pricing page</a> for the cloud RaaS platform.</p>
    </section>

